arStrings.szText: I was walkin' in the swamp, watchin' mushrooms bloom from a bird carcass, when I sensed it. A new thing. An unknown sickness. There it was - trapped in a rotten corpse. Calling to me. Begging to be cultivated.
Fascination and admiration, and a little obsession. Like an eccentric artist
I brought it to one of my corpse groves. The sickness spread. Feasting on the dead. Breathtakingly beautiful. But the Tree senses what harm it could do in another's hands.
Bitterness and sadness at mentioning the Tree
